---
title: "Deciding what matters"
description: "Develop your judgment and decision making skills and learn to guide value creation"
priority: 0.8
isDraft: false
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  {% include 'templates/_head.liquid' %}
  <body class="bg-white font-sans">
    {% include 'templates/_header.liquid' %}

    <div class="h-20"></div>

    <main class="min-h-screen">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <section class="relative container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl pt-24 pb-16 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-6 right-4 -rotate-25 select-none w-[180px] pointer-events-none z-0" aria-hidden="true">
          <img src="/assets/logo/schnuddel_clay.svg" class="w-[180px]">
        </div>
        <p class="relative z-10 text-lg text-sage3 font-medium tracking-wide uppercase mb-4 font-serif italic">
          Causable means capable of being the cause of something.
        </p>
        <h1 class="relative z-10 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif balanced pb-6">
          Deciding what matters
        </h1>
          <p class="text-xl max-w-xl pb-4">
            A guided development program for people who want to hone their judgment and
            decision-making skills to help teams and organizations create lasting value.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xl max-w-xl">
          The Causable Journey helps you unfold your agency.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xl max-w-xl pt-4">
          In this program, you learn:
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl max-w-xl">
          ... to create value that matters to both your organization and its customers
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl max-w-xl">
          ... to navigate uncertainty with sound judgment
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl max-w-xl">
          ... to help your organization build in a smart way that enables its strategy
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl max-w-xl">
          ... to proficiently guide decision-making, be it in collaboration with humans or AI agents
        </p>

         <p class="text-xl max-w-xl pb-4 pt-4">
          You don't just want any results. You want results that matter.
        </p>

      </section>

      <!-- Journey -->
      <section id="journey" class="relative pb-20">

        <!-- SVG curved path (desktop only) -->
        <div class="journey-path-container hidden md:block absolute inset-0 z-10 pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg class="journey-path-svg w-full h-full" viewBox="0 0 800 2950" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMin meet" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <!-- Segment 1: Full amplitude, bold (Steps 1–4) -->
            <path d="M 400 40
                     C 200 120, 200 200, 300 260
                     C 400 320, 600 320, 600 400
                     C 600 480, 400 500, 300 560
                     C 200 620, 200 700, 400 740"
              stroke="var(--color-clay3)" stroke-width="3" stroke-dasharray="14 8" stroke-linecap="round" />

            <!-- Segment 2: Full amplitude, medium (Steps 5–6) -->
            <path d="M 400 740
                     C 600 780, 600 840, 500 920
                     C 400 1000, 200 1000, 200 1080
                     C 200 1160, 400 1200, 400 1280"
              stroke="var(--color-clay3)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-dasharray="12 7" stroke-linecap="round" />

            <!-- Segment 3: Narrowing curves (Step 7) -->
            <path d="M 400 1280
                     C 400 1360, 260 1400, 330 1480
                     C 400 1520, 540 1520, 540 1540
                     C 540 1620, 410 1720, 350 1840"
              stroke="var(--color-clay3)" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="10 7" stroke-linecap="round" />

            <!-- Segment 4: Tight curves drifting right toward arrival (Steps 8–9) -->
            <path d="M 350 1840
                     C 310 1920, 320 2000, 400 2040
                     C 470 2080, 460 2140, 440 2180
                     C 410 2240, 340 2280, 340 2360
                     C 340 2430, 420 2480, 520 2510
                     C 640 2550, 720 2580, 740 2640
                     C 750 2680, 750 2710, 745 2740"
              stroke="var(--color-clay3)" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-dasharray="8 6" stroke-linecap="round" />

            <!-- Milestone dots (shrinking toward end) -->
            <circle cx="400" cy="40" r="7" fill="var(--color-clay3)" />
            <circle cx="600" cy="400" r="6" fill="var(--color-clay2)" />
            <circle cx="300" cy="560" r="6" fill="var(--color-clay3)" />
            <circle cx="400" cy="740" r="6" fill="var(--color-clay2)" />
            <circle cx="200" cy="1080" r="6" fill="var(--color-clay4)" />
            <circle cx="400" cy="1280" r="6" fill="var(--color-clay2)" />
            <circle cx="540" cy="1540" r="5" fill="var(--color-clay3)" />
            <circle cx="340" cy="2360" r="5" fill="var(--color-clay2)" />
            <circle cx="745" cy="2740" r="7" fill="var(--color-clay4)" />
          </svg>
        </div>

        <!-- Mobile vertical dotted line -->
        <div class="md:hidden absolute left-8 top-0 bottom-0 border-l-2 border-dashed pointer-events-none" style="border-color: var(--color-clay3);" aria-hidden="true"></div>

        <!-- Step 1: Our start: 1:1 Kickoffs — card above line, slightly transparent -->
        <div class="journey-step relative z-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
          <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
            <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8" style="background-color: rgba(249, 241, 239, 0.88)">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <img src="/assets/icons/icon_question_mark.svg" class="w-12 h-12 flex-shrink-0" width="48" height="48" alt="">
                <div>
                  <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-clay2 text-clay4 mb-3">
                    Your start
                  </span>
                  <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif pb-2">1:1 Kickoff</h3>
                  <p class="text-lg">
                    Your Causable Journey begins with a personal conversation. Together we explore
                    where you stand, what you will need in order to succeed in your planned endeavor,
                    and which skills you want to develop further over the coming months. We
                    map the resources you can already build on, and identify your next learning steps
                    on this leg of your journey.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="hidden md:block"></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2: How we explore together: Coaching Prompts — text above line, light white bg -->
        <div class="journey-step relative z-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
          <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
            <div class="hidden md:block"></div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl py-4 px-6" style="background-color: rgba(255, 252, 252, 0.78)">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <img src="/assets/icons/icon_spiral.svg" class="w-10 h-10 flex-shrink-0" width="40" height="40" alt="">
                <div>
                  <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-sage1 text-sage4 mb-3">
                    How we explore together
                  </span>
                  <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif pb-2">Coaching prompts</h3>
                  <p class="text-lg">
                    The journey is an interactive conversation that guides you through reflection
                    and helps you hone your judgment and decision-making skills.
                    We support you in structuring your approach and steering course on your development path
                    through coaching prompts that are designed to help you see more clearly.
                    Your tutor is always just one click away, at your side virtually at all times.
                    To better understand where your thinking is going, and how your personal explorations
                    went, we of course expect you to answer back.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3: Module 1 — band is background, text above line -->
        <div class="journey-step">
          <div class="bg-sage1 -rotate-1 h-[40px] -mb-5"></div>
          <div class="bg-sage1">
            <div class="relative z-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
              <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                  <img src="/assets/icons/icon_placemark.svg" class="w-12 h-12 flex-shrink-0" width="48" height="48" alt="">
                  <div>
                    <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-sage2 text-sage4 mb-3">
                      Sort your thoughts
                    </span>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif pb-2">Module 1</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg">
                      Learn to solve not just any problem. Identify the problems that matter.
                      Not everything that gives you a sense of achievement is actually worth spending
                      your energy and that of your organization. Learn to identify dependencies,
                      feedback loops and drivers of dynamics. Map out relevant stakeholders and choose how
                      to involve them in your decision process and solution creation. Learn to approach
                      problems smartly, and create value for others while you support your organization's strategic goals.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="hidden md:block"></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-sage1 rotate-1 h-[40px] -mt-5"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 4: Module 2  — text above line, light white bg -->
        <div class="journey-step relative z-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
          <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
            <div class="hidden md:block"></div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl py-4 px-6" style="background-color: rgba(255, 252, 252, 0.78)">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <img src="/assets/icons/icon_shaky_build.svg" class="w-10 h-10 flex-shrink-0" width="40" height="40" alt="">
                <div>
                  <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-sage1 text-sage4 mb-3">
                    Learn to explore and navigate uncertainty
                  </span>
                  <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif pb-2">Module 2</h3>
                  <p class="text-lg">
                    Develop discernment and choose your course of action by taking hypothesis-guided steps to solution generation.
                    Explore perspectives and challenge your thoughts and perceptions to find the overarching picture.
                    Orient yourself and others in the problem landscape and design informative interventions
                    that help you identify suitable steps to take. Become more proficient in judging what you know
                    and how to assess your options.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 5: Module 3 — band is background, text above line -->
        <div class="journey-step">
          <div class="bg-clay1 -rotate-1 h-[40px] -mb-5"></div>
          <div class="bg-clay1">
            <div class="relative z-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
              <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                  <img src="/assets/icons/icon_embrace.svg" class="w-12 h-12 flex-shrink-0" width="48" height="48" alt="">
                  <div>
                    <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-clay2 text-clay4 mb-3">
                      Identify leverage and organize for effective results
                    </span>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif pb-2">Module 3</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg">
                      Can it work? Identify suitable leverage points, smart actions and design useful interventions
                      to come up with solutions. Organize yourself and help others tackle the relevant problems, generate
                      solutions that support the strategic goals of your organization, and communicate effectively.
                      Do the doable and build from there.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="hidden md:block"></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-clay1 rotate-1 h-[40px] -mt-5"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 6: What if you get stuck? — text above line, light white bg -->
        <div class="journey-step relative z-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
          <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
            <div class="hidden md:block"></div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl py-4 px-6" style="background-color: rgba(255, 252, 252, 0.78)">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <img src="/assets/icons/icon_question_mark.svg" class="w-10 h-10 flex-shrink-0" width="40" height="40" alt="">
                <div>
                  <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-sage1 text-sage4 mb-3">
                    Upgrade option - additional 1:1s bookable upon request
                  </span>
                  <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif pb-2">1:1 Coaching to troubleshoot</h3>
                  <p class="text-lg">
                    Sometimes we seem to know what to do — and still feel that we can’t take action.
                    In this case, a 1:1 coaching can help you work through roadblocks and find your feasible next steps.
                    Personal sessions are available as an upgrade option.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 7: What expects you in the modules — band is background, text above line -->
        <div class="journey-step">
          <div class="bg-sage1 -rotate-1 h-[40px] -mb-5"></div>
          <div class="bg-sage1">
            <div class="relative z-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
              <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                  <img src="/assets/icons/icon_turnaround.svg" class="w-12 h-12 flex-shrink-0" width="48" height="48" alt="">
                  <div>
                    <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-sage2 text-sage4 mb-3">
                      How does this program work?
                    </span>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif pb-2">Background</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg">
                      The Causable Journey is based on a systemic transformative leadership and executive coaching
                      methodology developed at University of St. Gallen. We add training elements for those questions
                      that you can better handle when you understand some background on how humans make decisions and
                      explore their thoughts fruitfully, by themselves or together with others. If you go through this
                      program in a version that we offer through your employer, you will also practice certain skills in interactive peer groups.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-lg pt-3">
                      The core of this exercise relies on you going your personal path, trying your new skills out in the field, and returning
                      to reflect with us. The Causable Journey provides scaffolding based on scientific insights from neuroeconomics
                      on learning and decision-making. Its key steps are derived from years of learning, observing, teaching
                      joint decision-making in research and development and multiple industries, and of course, making actual
                      decisions on how to develop products, build new digital services and open up new markets.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-lg pt-3">
                      While you can engage with the program self-paced whenever your work week allows
                      (or when you look for some space to reflect together), it could typically take
                      between 3 and 12 months to make a noticeable step forward. This depends on how intensely
                      you can focus on your own development, and practice and reflect on your observations to build
                      and refine your judgment skills.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="hidden md:block"></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-sage1 rotate-1 h-[40px] -mt-5"></div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 8: Summary and learnings — card above line, slightly transparent -->
        <div class="journey-step relative z-20 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
          <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
            <div class="hidden md:block"></div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8" style="background-color: rgba(249, 241, 239, 0.88)">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <img src="/assets/icons/icon_idea.svg" class="w-12 h-12 flex-shrink-0" width="48" height="48" alt="">
                <div>
                  <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-clay2 text-clay4 mb-3">
                    Synthesize your insights
                  </span>
                  <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif pb-2">1:1 Summary</h3>
                  <p class="text-lg">
                    In a final personal coaching session, we help you synthesize everything
                    you have learned. Together we reflect on your insights so that you can distill them
                    into a clear, actionable approach that you can take forward.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 9: Case presentation — band is background, text above line -->
        <div class="journey-step">
          <div class="bg-primary4 -rotate-1 h-[40px] -mb-5"></div>
          <div class="bg-primary4 text-white py-16">
            <div class="relative z-20 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
              <img src="/assets/icons/icon_upwards.svg" class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto mb-4" width="64" height="64" alt="">
              <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium bg-primary3 text-white mb-4">
                Value added, ready to go
              </span>
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-serif pb-3">Your value creation case</h3>
              <p class="text-xl max-w-lg mx-auto">
                Here is where it all comes together. You have a case ready to present:
                what's in it for your organization, what's in it for the customer, how you will
                implement the solution you came up with together with your stakeholders,
                and how you can communicate it cogently. Along the way, you have honed
                your personal value creation approach —
                grounded in reflection, shaped by experience, and ready for daily use.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-primary4 rotate-1 h-[40px] -mt-5"></div>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Contact CTA -->
      <section class="js-contact container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl pt-16 mb-20">
        <div class="max-w-xl rounded-3xl p-4 bg-clay1 text-gray-700">
          <div class="js-contact-btn cursor-pointer">
            <h3 class="text-2xl pb-3">
              Interested in offering this program through your organization?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg">
              The program runs in small groups to ensure personal attention.
              Get in touch to learn about upcoming start dates and how the program
              can support you in developing your key contributors.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary3 underline pt-3">
              Get in touch
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="js-contact-form hidden text-left text-xl font-sans">
            {% include 'includes/_contact-form.liquid' checked: 'training' %}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>

    {% include 'templates/_footer.liquid' %}

    <script src="/assets/js/index.js"></script>
    <script src="/assets/js/scrollytelling.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
